The human body parts were found stashed in two polythene bags. [File, Standard]  Residents of Konate in Nyamira Town are reeling from shock after a man’s mutilated body was retrieved from two sacks dumped on the road by an unknown motorist.  Nyamira South Sub-County police commander Moses Kirong told The Standard that the two polythene sacks, black and red respectively, were thrown out of a speeding vehicle at the Kisii-Nyamira-Ikonge junction at 10pm.  Kirong said the human body parts had been cut into pieces and stashed in the sacks.  “The victim’s head was missing,” he said, pledging to conduct a probe into the bizarre incident.  How Nyamira County employees earned Sh2b irregularly  Baby who weighed 600g at birth 'in good health'  James Gesami sworn in as Nyamira Deputy Governor  Mentally ill suspect lynched over death of 90-year-old man Nyamira County Commissioner Amos Mariba said the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) detectives have taken up the matter, and would seek eyewitnesses’ accounts to help track down the suspects.  “The killers of this man would be known fairly soon,” said Mariba.  The body parts were taken to the Nyamira County Referral Hospital morgue.   Maiti yafukuliwa kisii baada ya mahakama kutoa agizo  Man kills wife and chops body parts in Nyamira County  Mke apatikana na makosa ya uzinzi mjini Nyamira By Olivia Odhiambo | 4 hours ago By Harold Odhiambo | 1 day ago By James Omoro | 1 day ago By Harold Odhiambo | 1 day ago